abstract: >-
  Companion paper to v6.0 (DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.18680957).
  Provides three theoretical contributions:
  (1) engagement with Hoel's impossibility theorem — trace.log
  as externalized continual learning;
  (2) mathematical grounding of PCO via Camlin's attractor dynamics;
  (3) awareness profiles (Meertens et al., 2026) replacing binary metrics.
  Maps independent convergent research. Specifies trace.log architecture,
  defines Control-B experiment, applies dimensional metrics retrospectively
  to v6 data (N=96, 8 architectures).
